        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(whatsapp): cache bot's own outbound messages for quote metadata (#91445)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Cache the bot's **own outbound** WhatsApp messages in the quote-metadata cache so a later user swipe-reply to one of those messages builds a correct `quoted.key`.\n- Fixes the bot's reply bubble silently failing to render on WhatsApp Desktop when a user swipe-replies to a message the bot itself sent.\n\n## Motivation\n\nCloses #91445.\n\n`cacheInboundMessageMeta(...)` was only called for **inbound** (user-sent) messages. The bot never cached metadata for its *own* outgoing messages. So when a user uses WhatsApp's native swipe-to-reply on one of the bot's bubbles, the outbound `getQuote()` path calls `lookupInboundMessageMeta(...)`, misses the cache, and the fallback defaults kick in:\n\n- `fromMe` defaults to `false`, even though the quoted message actually *was* sent by the bot (should be `true`).\n- `participant` falls back to the replying user's JID rather than the bot's own JID (the real sender of the quoted message).\n\nThe resulting Baileys `quoted.key` (`{ remoteJid, id, fromMe: false, participant: <wrong sender> }`) doesn't match the message WhatsApp Desktop has in its local store for that ID, so the Desktop client drops rendering of the reply bubble. Android is more lenient and renders it regardless. This matches the issue's observation that the bug only triggers when quoting the **bot's own** prior messages.\n\n## Fix\n\nImplements the issue's recommended primary fix (cache outbound messages). At the existing send choke point (`rememberOutboundMessage`, which already records the outbound message id for echo-suppression), also cache the quote metadata for that message via a new pure helper `buildOutboundQuotedMeta(...)`:\n\n- `fromMe: true`\n- `participant`: the bot's own JID (falling back to its LID) **for groups only** — omitted for direct chats, matching WhatsApp's quote semantics where direct-chat quotes carry no participant.\n- `body`: the trimmed outbound text for the quote preview bubble (dropped when empty).\n\nFuture swipe-reply lookups (`lookupInboundMessageMeta` / `lookupInboundMessageMetaForTarget`) then resolve a correct `quoted.key` for the bot's own messages. The metadata-independent send path is unchanged; this only adds a cache entry that previously didn't exist.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-whatsapp.config.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/quoted-message.test.ts` — **7 passed** (3 new)\n- Full WhatsApp extension suite: **85 files / 943 tests passed**\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.extensions.json --noEmit` — clean\n- oxlint (extensions tsconfig) on changed files — 0 warnings / 0 errors\n- `oxfmt --check` on changed files — clean\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed:** the bot's outbound message metadata is now cached with `fromMe:true` + bot participant, so a later swipe-reply resolves the correct quote key instead of the `fromMe:false` + replying-user fallback.\n- **Real environment:** Node v25, repo `vitest` v4.1.8.\n- **Exact commands run after the patch:**\n  ```\n  node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-whatsapp.config.ts extensions/whatsapp/src/quoted-message.test.ts\n  ```\n- **Captured output AFTER fix:**\n  ```\n   RUN  v4.1.8 /…/repos/openclaw\n   ✓ extension-whatsapp extensions/whatsapp/src/quoted-message.test.ts (7 tests) 26ms\n   Test Files  1 passed (1)\n        Tests  7 passed (7)\n  ```\n- **Regression test:** `extensions/whatsapp/src/quoted-message.test.ts` — the new cases assert that `buildOutboundQuotedMeta` produces `{ fromMe: true, participant: <bot JID> }` for groups (and the cached entry round-trips through `lookupInboundMessageMeta`), omits the participant for direct chats, and falls back to the bot's LID. These exercise behavior that did not exist before this change.\n- **What was NOT tested:** the live WhatsApp Desktop rendering itself (no live multi-device client in CI) — the issue is `clawsweeper:needs-live-repro`. The fix targets the documented root cause (cache miss → wrong `quoted.key`); the unit tests prove the cache now carries correct `fromMe`/`participant` for the bot's own messages.\n",
        "branch": "fix/91445-cache-outbound-quote-meta",
